  "text": "# Envoy Access Logging Configuration Audit (v1.31.2)\n\n## Summary\n\nThis audit identifies all C++ access log implementations and filters in Envoy v1.31.2, along with their structured (JSON) logging support.\n\n## Access Log Sink Implementations (Write Destinations)\n\n### 1. File Access Logger\n**Location**: `source/extensions/access_loggers/file/`\n**Proto Definition**: `envoy/extensions/access_loggers/file/v3/file.proto`\n**JSON Support**: YES - Full JSON support\n**Details**: \n- Supports multiple output formats via `FileAccessLog` sink\n- Implements `kFormat` (text), `kJsonFormat` (deprecated), `kTypedJsonFormat`, and `kLogFormat` options\n- Uses `SubstitutionFormatStringUtils::createJsonFormatter()` for JSON formatting\n- Handles both simple text format strings and complex structured JSON with typed values\n\n### 2. Stream Access Loggers (stdout/stderr)\n**Location**: `source/extensions/access_loggers/stream/`\n**Proto Definitions**: \n- `envoy/extensions/access_loggers/stream/v3/stream.proto` (StdoutAccessLog, StderrAccessLog)\n**JSON Support**: YES - JSON support through SubstitutionFormatString\n**Details**:\n- Implementations: `StdoutAccessLogFactory` and `StderrAccessLogFactory`\n- Reuses `FileAccessLog` implementation with stdout/stderr destinations\n- Supports `log_format` field using SubstitutionFormatString for flexible output formatting\n- Can produce both text and JSON output\n\n### 3. gRPC HTTP Access Logger\n**Location**: `source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/http_grpc_access_log_impl.h`\n**Proto Definition**: `envoy/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/v3/als.proto` (HttpGrpcAccessLogConfig)\n**JSON Support**: YES - Structured protobuf format\n**Details**:\n- Streams HTTP access logs via gRPC using `HttpGrpcAccessLog` class\n- Sends `envoy::data::accesslog::v3::HTTPAccessLogEntry` messages\n- Uses structured protobuf message format (inherently structured)\n- Supports additional headers, trailers, and filter state logging\n- Includes custom tags support for structured metadata\n\n### 4. gRPC TCP Access Logger\n**Location**: `source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/tcp_grpc_access_log_impl.h`\n**Proto Definition**: `envoy/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/v3/als.proto` (TcpGrpcAccessLogConfig)\n**JSON Support**: YES - Structured protobuf format\n**Details**:\n- Streams TCP access logs via gRPC using `TcpGrpcAccessLog` class\n- Sends `envoy::data::accesslog::v3::TCPAccessLogEntry` messages\n- Uses structured protobuf message format\n- Similar configuration to HTTP variant with CommonGrpcAccessLogConfig\n\n### 5. Fluentd Access Logger\n**Location**: `source/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/`\n**Proto Definition**: `envoy/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/v3/fluentd.proto`\n**JSON Support**: YES - Structured msgpack format with JSON-like nested objects\n**Details**:\n- Sends access logs via TCP to Fluentd using Forward Protocol\n- Uses `FluentdAccessLog` class for log emission\n- Supports `google.protobuf.Struct record` field for structured key-value pairs\n- Values rendered as strings, numbers, or booleans\n- Supports nested JSON objects from operators like FILTER_STATE and DYNAMIC_METADATA\n- Implements buffering and connection retry logic\n\n### 6. OpenTelemetry Access Logger\n**Location**: `source/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/`\n**Proto Definition**: `envoy/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/v3/logs_service.proto`\n**JSON Support**: YES - Structured format with typed fields\n**Details**:\n- Sends access logs via gRPC or HTTP using OTLP (OpenTelemetry Protocol)\n- Uses `AccessLog` class in OpenTelemetry namespace\n- Supports `opentelemetry.proto.common.v1.KeyValueList` for attributes\n- Supports `opentelemetry.proto.common.v1.AnyValue` for body field\n- Includes resource attributes for Envoy node info\n- Can disable built-in labels and support custom tags\n- Uses `OpenTelemetryFormatter` for flexible attribute and body formatting\n\n### 7. Wasm Access Logger\n**Location**: `source/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/`\n**Proto Definition**: `envoy/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/v3/wasm.proto`\n**JSON Support**: DEPENDS - Determined by WASM plugin\n**Details**:\n- Generic wrapper using `WasmAccessLog` class\n- Delegates logging to dynamically loaded WASM module\n- Format determined by WASM plugin implementation\n- Supports access log filtering before WASM invocation\n- Format is configurable within the WASM module\n\n## Access Log Filter Implementations (Filtering Decisions)\n\nThese classes filter which requests should be logged (return true = log, false = skip):\n\n### Core Filters (in `source/common/access_log/`)\n\n1. **StatusCodeFilter** - Filters based on HTTP response status code using comparison operators\n2. **DurationFilter** - Filters based on total request/response duration in milliseconds\n3. **NotHealthCheckFilter** - Filters out health check requests\n4. **TraceableRequestFilter** - Logs only requests marked as traceable and service-forced\n5. **RuntimeFilter** - Filters based on runtime feature keys with percentage-based sampling\n6. **HeaderFilter** - Filters based on request header presence and values\n7. **ResponseFlagFilter** - Filters based on Envoy response flags (errors, timeouts, etc.)\n8. **GrpcStatusFilter** - Filters based on gRPC status codes (with HTTP status fallback)\n9. **LogTypeFilter** - Filters based on access log type (HTTP, TCP, etc.)\n10. **MetadataFilter** - Filters based on dynamic metadata presence or values\n11. **AndFilter** - Logical AND composition of sub-filters\n12. **OrFilter** - Logical OR composition of sub-filters\n\n### Extension Filters\n\n13. **CEL Filter** (in `source/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/`)\n   - Evaluates Common Expression Language (CEL) expressions\n   - Location: `source/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/cel.h` (CELAccessLogExtensionFilter)\n   - Proto: `envoy/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/v3/cel.proto`\n   - Supports string conversion, concatenation, and manipulation functions\n   - Enables complex conditional logging based on request/response attributes\n\n## Proto Definitions Without C++ Implementations (v1.31.2)\n\nThe following proto definitions exist in data-plane-api but lack C++ implementations in this Envoy version:\n\n1. **Stats Access Logger**\n   - Proto: `envoy/extensions/access_loggers/stats/v3/stats.proto`\n   - Type: Access log sink that emits custom Envoy statistics\n   - Features: Configurable counters and histograms with tags and command operator values\n   - Status: Proto defined but no C++ implementation in v1.31.2\n\n2. **Dynamic Modules Access Logger**\n   - Proto: `envoy/extensions/access_loggers/dynamic_modules/v3/dynamic_modules.proto`\n   - Type: Access log sink for custom behavior via dlopen-loaded modules\n   - Features: Shared module loading, per-logger naming, flexible configuration via google.protobuf.Any\n   - Status: Proto defined but no C++ implementation in v1.31.2\n\n3. **Process RateLimit Filter**\n   - Proto: `envoy/extensions/access_loggers/filters/process_ratelimit/v3/process_ratelimit.proto`\n   - Type: Access log filter for global token bucket-based rate limiting\n   - Features: Dynamic token bucket configuration via ConfigSource\n   - Status: Proto defined but no C++ implementation in v1.31.2\n\n## JSON/Structured Logging Support Summary\n\n| Component | Type | JSON Support | Format |\n|-----------|------|--------------|--------|\n| File | Sink | YES | Text, JSON, Typed JSON |\n| Stdout/Stderr | Sink | YES | SubstitutionFormatString (text/JSON) |\n| gRPC HTTP | Sink | YES | Structured Protobuf (HTTPAccessLogEntry) |\n| gRPC TCP | Sink | YES | Structured Protobuf (TCPAccessLogEntry) |\n| Fluentd | Sink | YES | Structured MessagePack with JSON nesting |\n| OpenTelemetry | Sink | YES | Structured OTLP (KeyValueList, AnyValue) |\n| Wasm | Sink | DEPENDS | Plugin-defined |\n| CEL Filter | Filter | N/A | Expression-based selection |\n| Status Code | Filter | N/A | Comparison-based selection |\n| Duration | Filter | N/A | Numeric comparison-based selection |\n| Health Check | Filter | N/A | Boolean flag-based selection |\n\n## Key Architectural Notes\n\n1. **Base Class Hierarchy**: All sink implementations extend `Common::ImplBase` which handles filter evaluation before `emitLog()` call\n2. **Formatter Integration**: Most sinks use `Formatter::FormatterPtr` for flexible output formatting\n3. **Thread Safety**: Access loggers use thread-local storage via `ThreadLocal::SlotPtr` for efficient per-thread instances\n4. **Protobuf Messaging**: gRPC and OpenTelemetry loggers use structured protobuf messages for data transmission\n5. **Filter Extensibility**: `ExtensionFilterFactory` allows custom filter implementations (like CEL)\n6. **Configuration Factory Pattern**: Each access logger has a factory class implementing `AccessLogInstanceFactory`\n\n## Conclusion\n\nEnvoy v1.31.2 provides comprehensive access logging coverage with multiple sink implementations supporting both unstructured text logging and structured (JSON/protobuf) logging. The architecture is extensible via factory pattern and supports composition of filters through AND/OR operators. All major sink types (file, gRPC, Fluentd, OpenTelemetry, Wasm) support structured data in their respective formats."
}

